Quote:  <i>Bunk</i>, probably American in origin, was early in use in New Zealand. Edward Jerningham Wakefield felt it necessary to describe it as a `wooden shelf' for his readers, when he found it in use here.
Notes:  [see also MAORI BUNK (trampers')] Ruth Mason `Track and Trail'

